{"parse":{"title":"Petty tyranny","pageid":2880062,"revid":843376511,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Petty tyranny</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-ashforth_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ashforth-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> (or <b>petty authority</b> or <b>petty dictator</b> or <b>petty power</b>) is authority exercised by a <a href=\"/wiki/Leadership\" title=\"Leadership\">leader</a>, usually one unchosen by the led, in a relatively limited or an intimate environment, such as that exercised by a fellow peer of a social group.  It is a <a href=\"/wiki/Pejorative\" title=\"Pejorative\">pejorative</a> term, that carries with it a sense of authority that was gained, or is used, in an unfair or capricious manner.\n</p><p>Ashforth discussed potentially destructive sides of leadership and identified petty tyrants, i.e. leaders who exercise a tyrannical style of management, resulting in a <a href=\"/wiki/Climate_of_fear\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Climate of fear\">climate of fear</a> in the workplace.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ashforth_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ashforth-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He proposed the following six characteristics to define petty tyranny:<sup id=\"cite_ref-Haslam2004_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Haslam2004-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-RiceCooper2010_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-RiceCooper2010-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<ol><li><a href=\"/wiki/Arbitrariness\" title=\"Arbitrariness\">arbitrariness</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Self-aggrandizement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Self-aggrandizement\">self-aggrandizement</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Belittling\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Belittling\">belittling</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/Subordinates\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Subordinates\">subordinates</a></li>\n<li>lack of consideration for others</li>\n<li>a forcing style of <a href=\"/wiki/Conflict_resolution\" title=\"Conflict resolution\">conflict resolution</a></li>\n<li>discouragement of <a href=\"/wiki/Initiative\" title=\"Initiative\">initiative</a></li>\n<li><span class=\"clarify-content\" style=\"padding-left:0.1em; padding-right:0.1em; color:#595959; border:1px solid #DDD;\">non-<a href=\"/wiki/Contingent\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Contingent\">contingent</a></span><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Clarify\" style=\"margin-left:0.1em; white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Please_clarify\" title=\"Wikipedia:Please clarify\"><span title=\"This passage needs to be better explained. (July 2015)\">clarify</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> use of <a href=\"/wiki/Punishment\" title=\"Punishment\">punishment</a></li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Petty_tyranny&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"div-col columns column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Abusive_power_and_control\" title=\"Abusive power and control\">Abusive power and control</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Abusive_supervision\" title=\"Abusive supervision\">Abusive supervision</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Kick_the_cat\" title=\"Kick the cat\">Kick the cat</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Kiss_up_kick_down\" title=\"Kiss up kick down\">Kiss up kick down</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Machiavellianism_in_the_workplace\" title=\"Machiavellianism in the workplace\">Machiavellianism in the workplace</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Narcissism_in_the_workplace\" title=\"Narcissism in the workplace\">Narcissism in the workplace</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Psychopathy_in_the_workplace\" title=\"Psychopathy in the workplace\">Psychopathy in the workplace</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Toxic_leader\" title=\"Toxic leader\">Toxic leader</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Workplace_bullying\" title=\"Workplace bullying\">Workplace bullying</a></li></ul></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Petty_tyranny&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-ashforth-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-ashforth_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-ashforth_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Petty tyranny in organizations </i>, Ashforth, Blake, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Human_Relations\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Human Relations\">Human Relations</a></i>, Vol. 47, No. 7, 755-778 (1994)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Haslam2004-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Haslam2004_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">S Alexander Haslam (2004). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=XPCdpv2nwmYC&amp;pg=PA142\"><i>Psychology in Organizations</i></a>. SAGE. p.&#160;142. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-7619-4231-3\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-7619-4231-3\">978-0-7619-4231-3</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Psychology+in+Organizations&amp;rft.pages=142&amp;rft.pub=SAGE&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7619-4231-3&amp;rft.au=S+Alexander+Haslam&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D